SIMPLE: salutatorian
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Salutatorian
<hw>Sa*lu`ta*to"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The student
who pronounces the salutatory oration at the annual Commencement or like
exercises of a college, -- an honor commonly assigned to that member of
the graduating class who ranks second in scholarship.</def>
<mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salutatorily</ent>⟦br⟧
